		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30501127">Outside of a few pompadoured protagonist-featuring exceptions like Redline and Space Dandy, anime is not made for you, the western viewer. We can easily get more specific: Paniponi Dash, for example, was not made for inexperienced anime viewers. Diabolik Lovers was not made for anyone outside of its niche audience of masochistic abusecore enthusiasts, and likewise Aikatsu was not made for anyone even remotely close to the age of 20 (ie. anybody reading this post). But this isn't just an issue of demographics—the phenomenon of the average western anime viewer watching anime in vastly different circumstances than originally intended manifests itself in numerous other, perhaps subtler, ways as well: Spirited Away was not made for a 13.3 inch lcd display with poor color reproduction. Bakemonogatari was not made to be watched with subtitles. Akira was not made for those shitty white iPod headphones. City Hunter was not made to be watched in one sitting.[1] The context in which we experience any given anime (or manga) is enormous in scope and includes both how the show is presented to us and the (not so) simple fact of who we are as people. Both typically differ significantly from what the creators of any given anime envisioned and planned for. What are some of the challenges we face when attempting to enjoy and evaluate anime? How can we mitigate the severity of these issues and we even have some sort of duty to do so in the first place?<br />
<br />
Alternatively, when we eschew shows made explicitly for 16-30 year-old westerners living in the Hulu-Netflix-DVR age and watch chinese cartoons that air at two-in-the-morning why should we have any sort of expectations at all when they aren't made for us in any way, shape, or form?<br />
<br />
<span style="font-size: 70%;">1. Jiri, Rido. <em>irc.rizon.net/#critics-conn</em>, Internet Relay Chat, 2013, Line 4924.<!--size--></span></div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/tCa2eBH.png" /><br />
<span style="color:#f3e7dd">join the quietly discursive at <!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">quiet discourse</a> || <!--link--><a href="http://twin-bells.tumblr.com/" rel="nofollow">tumblr</a><!--color--></span><!--center--></div></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
