That's probably why I don't "get" works like Devilman. When it came out it was a big deal but when I read it I was disappointed. I appreciate that it inspired other works but as a stand alone piece I think it's bad. I'm not impacted the same way as a person in the 70s would be. I'm not impacted the same way a person Japanese teen with fiery hormones in the 70s would be.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
